 If 
\begin_inset Formula $k\neq0$
\end_inset


\begin_inset Formula 
\[
N=\left[\begin{array}{cc}
ka & 0\\
0 & 1
\end{array}\right]\left[\begin{array}{cc}
1 & 0\\
kb & 1
\end{array}\right]\left[\begin{array}{cc}
1 & 0\\
0 & 0
\end{array}\right]\left[\begin{array}{cc}
1 & \frac{\ell}{k}\\
0 & 1
\end{array}\right]=\left[\begin{array}{cc}
ka & \ell a\\
kb & \ell b
\end{array}\right]
\]

\end_inset

and if 
\begin_inset Formula $k=0$
